      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Corinthians 15:20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") preserving the notion of the permanent significance of that personal experience of Jesus. In the other passage, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Romans 1:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", in which St. Paul distinctly alludes to our Lord’s human ancestry, the phrase ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "τοῦ γενομένου ἐκ σπέρματος Δαυεὶδ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " has a directly historical and polemical intention, as expressing and emphasising the human nature of Christ in antithesis to His Divinity. Here ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἐκ σπερμ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Δ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". merely expresses the fact of His humanity. We cannot affirm with certainty that the phrase has the Messianic import that ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Song of Solomon of David",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " has in the Gospels.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "κατὰ τὸ εὐαγγέλιόν μου",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ": ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The Gospel preached by me",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". See reff., and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "τὸ εὐ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "τὸ εὐαγγελισθὲν ὑπʼ ἐμοῦ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Galatians 1:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Corinthians 15:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), which of course is identical in substance with ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "τὸ εὐ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".… ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ὃ ἐπιστεύθην ἐγώ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Timothy 1:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). The verity both of Christ’s humanity and of His resurrection was emphasised in the Gospel preached by St. Paul. This is brought out by the punctuation of R.V.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
