  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Cambridge Bible for Schools and Colleges",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Consider what I say",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] ‘Apply the parable’; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "for our Lord",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—the Great Teacher of parables—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "shall give thee understanding",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The ms. authority requires the future indicative instead of aorist optative. The verb belonging to our substantive here ‘understanding’ is used by our Lord in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 13:51",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", after all His parables of the kingdom of heaven, ‘Have ye understood all these things?’ and the corresponding adjective in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 15:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ‘And Peter answered and said unto Him, Declare unto us the parable. And He said, Are ye also even yet without understanding?’",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Bengel's Gnomen",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Timothy 2:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Νόει",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "attend to, consider",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", what I say: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "σύνεσις",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "understanding",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", is of the divine gift; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "νοεῖν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "to consider",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", is the part of a well-minded man. Paul says this, if you compare ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Timothy 2:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " with ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Timothy 2:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". If the husbandman (Timothy) hath (or ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "shall have",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") laboured, then first he ought (he is entitled) to partake of the fruits (in which the resurrection of Christ abounds, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Timothy 2:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Timothy 2:11-12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "); but if this were the whole meaning of Paul, he would have said, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "τὸν μεταληψόμενον δεῖ κοπιᾷν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Therefore from this seventh verse we may gather that a thought rather different is involved in this expression, which amounts to this:—Paul trained the mind of Timothy, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Timothy 1:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; therefore fruits are chiefly due to him from Timothy. In this view, Paul does not openly require, as is necessary in addressing dull men, but by amphibology and enigma, that Timothy should ingenuously acknowledge and perform the duty; and this he does by three comparisons taken from the employment of the soldier, the wrestler, the husbandman.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "δῴη γὰρ σοι",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "for may",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " the Lord ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "give to thee",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") The meaning is, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "He will give;",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " there is thus a connection between ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "consider",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "for;",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " but affection adds the modus or ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἧθος",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " [see Append. on “Modalis Sermo.” Here the imperative ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "mood",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " expresses the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "feeling",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "].—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ὁ Κύριος",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the Lord",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") Christ.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἐν πᾶσι",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "in all things",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "He had",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " already ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "given",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " him understanding ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "in many things:",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " this being taken for granted, Paul says, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "May He give it in all things",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 7.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "For the Lord shall give",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " for ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "and the Lord give",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", A.V. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Consider what I say. The",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " apostle's lessons had been given in parables or similitudes. He therefore begs Timothy to note them well, lest the application to himself should escape him, suggesting further that he should seek the necessary wisdom and understanding from God. So our Lord, at the end of the parables recorded in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", says to his disciples in ver. 51, \"Have ye understood all these things?\" and elsewhere, \"He that hath ears to hear, let him hear.\" ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Understanding",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "σύνεσιν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "); one of the special gifts of the Spirit (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Isaiah 11:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", LXX.; see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Colossians 1:9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Colossians 2:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). 2 Timothy 2:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Vincent's Word Studies",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Consider (νόει)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Better, understand.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And the Lord give thee understanding (δώσει γάρ ὁ κύριος σύνεσιν)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "More correctly, for the Lord shall give. For σύνεσιν understanding, see on Mark 12:33; see on Luke 2:47; see on Colossians 1:9. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "More correctly, for the Lord shall give. For σύνεσιν understanding, see on ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Mark 12:33",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; see on ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Luke 2:47",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; see on ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Colossians 1:9",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
